parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust manifold bolts can cause the exhaust manifold to separate from the engine, leading to a loud noise, loss of power, and potentially a vehicle fire. This can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Loud noise from the exhaust system
rattling or marbles sound from the exhaust
smoke coming from the hood
check engine light on
loss of power
engine stalling
intermittent sticking in 1st gear (automatic transmission).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
engine overheating
smoke coming from the hood
check engine light on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to lose structural integrity, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal consequences.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion of the frame
particularly in the rear wheel area
holes in the frame
sagging bumper
and a soft or spongy feeling when driving over bumps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle mounting can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and potentially fatal consequences.
symptoms: Rear axle moves and changes direction when accelerating
braking
or going over bumps
causing the vehicle to pull to one side or lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: These issues can cause inconvenience, discomfort, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Automatic lock malfunction
nuts breaking off hatchback hydraulic cylinder
hole developing in the floor
trunk design flaw
paint peeling off the roof
and rear hatchback hydraulic cylinder failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission slips or hesitates while shifting
transmission fails to shift into gear

transmission fails to accelerate
transmission warning lights or messages appear on the dashboard.
